# wormhook-scan roots — one path or glob per line; blank lines and # comments ignored.
#
# This is the SAMPLE. `wormhook-scan config --init` copies it to
#   ${XDG_CONFIG_HOME:-~/.config}/wormhook/scan-roots
# which each teammate edits for their own machine. Globs expand at scan time
# (a leading ~ becomes $HOME). Root globs must not contain spaces.
#
# Point these at wherever you keep cloned repos. Examples:

# ~/sandbox/git-repos/*/
# ~/sandbox/git-repos/*/*/
# ~/code/
# ~/work/
